  "prompt": "Put on red and live a little hindi meaning?",
  "response": "The phrase \"**Put on red and live a little**\" encourages someone to dress in red and enjoy life more freely or take some risks. Here's its translation in Hindi:\n\n### Hindi Translation:\n**\"\u0932\u093e\u0932 \u092a\u0939\u0928\u0947\u0902 \u0914\u0930 \u091c\u093c\u0930\u093e \u092e\u091c\u093c\u0947 \u0915\u0930\u0947\u0902\u0964\"**\n\n### Transliteration:\n**\"Laal pehnen aur zara maaze karein.\"**\n\n### Breakdown:\n- **\u0932\u093e\u0932 (Laal):** Red\n- **\u092a\u0939\u0928\u0947\u0902 (Pehnen):** Wear/put on\n- **\u0914\u0930 (Aur):** And\n- **\u091c\u093c\u0930\u093e (Zara):** A little\n- **\u092e\u091c\u093c\u0947 \u0915\u0930\u0947\u0902 (Maaze Karein):** Enjoy/have fun\n\n### Contextual Explanation:\n- **\u0932\u093e\u0932 \u092a\u0939\u0928\u0947\u0902 (Laal pehnen):** Suggests dressing in red, which is often associated with confidence, passion, and energy in many cultures, including Hindi-speaking ones.\n- **\u091c\u093c\u0930\u093e \u092e\u091c\u093c\u0947 \u0915\u0930\u0947\u0902 (Zara maaze karein):** Encourages taking some time to enjoy life, try new things, or break from routine.\n\n### Usage Example:\n- **English:** It's been a long week. Put on red and live a little!\n- **Hindi:** \u092f\u0947 \u0939\u092b\u094d\u0924\u093e \u092d\u0930 \u0915\u093e \u0925\u093e\u0964 \u0932\u093e\u0932 \u092a\u0939\u0928\u0947\u0902 \u0914\u0930 \u091c\u093c\u0930\u093e \u092e\u091c\u093c\u0947 \u0915\u0930\u0947\u0902!\n\nThis translation maintains the motivational and encouraging tone of the original phrase.",
